{
  "texts": [
    "In Ceseracciu et al. (2010), the authors explore the use of an SVM for identifying locomotion intentions from surface electromyography (sEMG) data.",
    "The study uses a phase-dependent approach, which is based on foot contact and foot push-off events, to contextualize muscle activation signals.",
    "The study demonstrates good accuracy on experimental data from three healthy subjects.",
    "The classification accuracy is also tested for different subsets of EMG features and muscles, to identify the minimal setup required for the control of an EMG-based exoskeleton for rehabilitation purposes.",
    "The study shows that SVM can be used to accurately identify locomotion intentions from sEMG data."
  ]
}